HEADWORD: Strato-cumulus
<hw>Stra`to-cu"mu*lus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Stratus</ets> + <ets>cumulus</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Meteor.)</fld> <def>Large balls or rolls of dark cloud which
frequently cover the whole sky, esp. in winter, and give it at times an
undulated appearance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

